"n.陶瓷制品；a.陶器的 无 n. 陶瓷(一种坚硬、易碎、抗热、防腐材料, 在高温下烧制的一种非金属矿物, 如由粘土制成); 陶器 【记】ce色, ram词根: 羊－彩色的羊－丰饶角(是用陶瓷做的) 【参】ceramics(n 制陶业); ceram(n 陶瓷); ceramist(n 陶艺家) 【类】mosaic: ceramic = patchwork: cloth马赛克是陶瓷片的拼合 = 拼缝物是布料的拼合shard: ceramic = crumb: cake 陶瓷碎片: 陶瓷制品 = 碎屑: 蛋糕 无 ceramic (adj.)  1850, keramic, from Greek keramikos, from keramos ""potter's clay, pottery, tiles,"" perhaps from a pre-Hellenic word. Watkins suggests possible connection with Latin cremare ""to burn,"" but Klein's sources are firmly against this. Spelling influenced by French céramique (1806). Related: ceramist (1855). Ceramics is attested from 1857."
